ials.','One half-course in film, video or performance useful but not required.'),(154,'GOV',2105,NULL,'Comparative Politics: Field Seminar','Surveys topics in comparative politics (both the developed and the developing world), including the rise of the modern state; institutions of government; interest mediation; democracy and authoritarianism; revolution; political parties; mass and elite political behavior; political economy.','Preference given to FAS Government graduate students.'),(158,'NEUROBIO',397,NULL,'Nervous System Construction and Function',NULL,NULL),(167,'NEC',97,'r','Group Tutorial - Sophomore Year','An introduction to the cultures and literatures of the Near East in ancient, classical, and modern times, emphasizing major themes and problems that cut across individual cultures and historical periods.',NULL),(168,'SEMPHIL',200,'r','Comparative Semitic Grammar: Seminar','Topic for 2011-12: To be determined.',NULL),(173,'FRENCH',97,NULL,'Tutorial-Sophomore Year: The Politics of Poetics: An Introduction to Literary and Cultural Analysis','An introduction to literary and cultural interpretation as it has evolved in French Studies since WWII. Our conversations will be structured around rigorous analysis of key literary works in relation to literary theory, semiotics, psychoanalysis, and politics.','Required of concentrators in French and Francophone Studies in their sophomore year. May also be taken as the Sophomore Tutorial by concentrators in Romance Studies. Open to non-concentrators with permission of course head.'),(181,'GOV',1002,NULL,'Advanced Quantitative Political Methodology','Introduces theories of inference underlying most statistical methods and how new approaches are developed. Examples include discrete choice, event counts, durations, missing data, ecological inference, time-series cross sectional analysis, compositional data, causal inference, and others.',NULL),(184,'NEUROBIO',346,NULL,'Visual Processing in Primates',NULL,NULL),(187,'E-PSCI'