s theorem, Fourier series, differentiation in several variables. Additional topics, including the classical results of vector calculus in two and three dimensions, as time allows.','There will be a heavy workload. This course, when taken for a letter grade, meets the General Education requirement for Empirical and Mathematical Reasoning or the Core area requirement for Quantitative Reasoning.'),(1591,'CELLBIO',346,NULL,'Molecular Basis of Human Disease',NULL,NULL),(1592,'SCAND',97,NULL,'Tutorial - Sophomore Year','Group or individual tutorial designed to supplement course work and acquaint students with appropriate analytical methods.','Open to concentrators in the Scandinavian option. Permission of the Director of Undergraduate Studies required.'),(1598,'HAA',271,'x','The Origins of Modernity: The \"New\" 18th Century','Issues include: art and the public sphere; the birth of the critic; high & low; interiors and interiority; intimacy; artistic identity; sexuality, sexual difference, and gender; the discourse of race. Emphasis on new research and methodologies.',NULL),(1619,'IMUNOL',358,NULL,'Self-renewal and Lineage Commitment of Hematopoietic Stem Cells',NULL,NULL),(1623,'NEUROBIO',332,NULL,'Ligand-Gated Ion Channels: Structure and Function',NULL,NULL),(1625,'MANCHU',NULL,'B','Elementary Manchu','Readings in a variety of historical and literary texts with emphasis on Manchu documentary sources, with and without diacritical marks.',NULL),(1627,'PHYSICS',347,'b','Topics in Quantum Optics',NULL,NULL),(1628,'COMPSCI',314,NULL,'Visual Computing',NULL,NULL),(1639,'ENG-SCI',390,NULL,'Environmental Chemistry',NULL,NULL),(1650,'STAT',340,NULL,'Random Network Models','Random graph models for biological, social, and information networks, including fixed degree, exponential, power law, small world, and geometric random graphs. Estimation and sampling methods for network data.',NULL),(1657,'SLAVIC',NULL,'Bab','Intermediate Russian (Intensive)','Covers essentially the same mate